The evidence with the title 'Robert E. Lee Day - Wikipedia ' says Robert E. Lee Day, also called Lee's Birthday, is a public holiday commemorating the birth of Robert E. Lee, observed each year on the third monday in january. Because Lee was the general in chief of the Armies Of The Confederacy, it is mainly observed in the U.S. South, particularly in Alabama and Mississippi.  ... In Alabama and Mississippi, it is celebrated together with Martin Luther King, ... 
